{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "02", "m": "11", "Y": "2025"}, "time": {"H": "12", "M": "16", "S": "26"}}, "news": [{"title": "Mangaluru: \u20b9135 crore tender floated for tech park under PPP model", "para": "Mangaluru, the 'Silicon Beach of India', is set to get its first purpose-built tech park. Karnataka State Electronics Development Corporation (KEONICS) has floated a Rs 135 crore tender for the project, which will be developed under a public-private partnership (PPP) model.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/commercial/mangaluru-launches-135-crore-tech-park-tender-to-boost-job-creation-and-sustainability/125033558?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-13510/125033558.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "commercial"}, {"title": "NGT directs MoEFCC to review environmental clearance for Gurugram housing project", "para": "The National Green Tribunal has stepped in, instructing the Union Environment Ministry to reassess the environmental clearance for a proposed housing project expansion in Gurugram. This decision arises from challenges brought forth by a resident welfare group.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/ngt-directs-moefcc-to-review-environmental-clearance-for-gurugram-housing-project/125032887?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-46782/125032887.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}, {"title": "No 40% circle rate hike now, but Ghaziabad tweaks shop rates", "para": "Ghaziabad administration has shelved a proposed 40% property circle rate hike, opting for minor technical corrections instead. The decision comes after a drop in property registrations, with officials aiming to avoid further revenue decline. Existing rates largely remain from 2024, with slight increases for small commercial properties."